# Environment Variables Configuration

# Copy this file to .env and fill in your actual values
# Never commit .env to version control!

# ============================================
# Google Analytics
# ============================================
# Get your Measurement ID from: https://analytics.google.com
# Format: G-XXXXXXXXXX
VITE_GA_MEASUREMENT_ID=G-XXXXXXXXXX

# ============================================
# EmailJS Configuration
# ============================================
# Sign up at: https://www.emailjs.com
# Get these values from your EmailJS dashboard

# Public Key (User ID)
VITE_EMAILJS_PUBLIC_KEY=your_public_key_here

# Service ID
VITE_EMAILJS_SERVICE_ID=your_service_id_here

# Template ID for Contact Form
VITE_EMAILJS_CONTACT_TEMPLATE_ID=your_contact_template_id_here

# Template ID for Newsletter Subscription
VITE_EMAILJS_NEWSLETTER_TEMPLATE_ID=your_newsletter_template_id_here

# ============================================
# Setup Instructions
# ============================================

## Google Analytics Setup:
# 1. Go to https://analytics.google.com
# 2. Create a new GA4 property
# 3. Copy your Measurement ID (format: G-XXXXXXXXXX)
# 4. Replace the ID in /index.html AND in /src/utils/analytics.js
# 5. Replace VITE_GA_MEASUREMENT_ID above

## EmailJS Setup:
# 1. Sign up at https://www.emailjs.com (free tier: 200 emails/month)
# 2. Create a new email service (Gmail, Outlook, etc.)
# 3. Create two email templates:
#    - Contact Form Template (for /contact page)
#    - Newsletter Template (for newsletter signups)
# 4. Copy your Public Key, Service ID, and Template IDs
# 5. Replace the placeholder values above
# 6. Uncomment the emailService.js integration in Contact.jsx and NewsletterSignup.jsx

